author: Inside Edition
description: A 2-year-old girl got her head stuck in banister bars. Mother Valerie Collins rushed down the stairs to find the scary scene as the toddler wailed. Collins realized she needed help and called 911. Five minutes later, the cavalry arrived. The firefighters used a special power tool to force the bars apart until finally, little Amora was free. She was left with a little scrape. Inside Edition spoke to Collins at her home outside Columbus, Ohio.
title: Firefighters Free 2-Year-Old Girl Who Got Her Head Stuck In Railing

author: Inside Edition
description: The notorious Tinder Swindler is out of jail and speaking exclusively with Inside Edition. Simon Leviev was arrested in the eastern European nation of Georgia two months ago after a woman claimed he swindled her out of $60,000. The 2022 Netflix documentary "The Tinder Swindler" turned Leviev into an international phenomenon. Now, Leviev says he's ready to settle down and is even thinking of starting his own dating app. Leviev continues to deny any wrongdoing.
title: 'The Tinder Swindler' Speaks Out In Inside Edition Exclusive Interview

author: Inside Edition
description: Mercedes Wells was in an emergency room while in labor when she says she was told to go home. Video shows Wells being wheeled out with instructions to wait at home for her labor to progress. She ended up giving birth inside her husband's truck on the side of an Indiana road. It happened just 8 minutes after they left the hospital. In a statement, the hospital, Franciscan Health says they are reviewing the video as part of a "thorough investigation into this alleged incident."
title: Woman Discharged From Hospital Gives Birth In Car Minutes Later

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition’s Eva Pilgrim speaks with longtime Murdaugh housekeeper Blanca Turrubiate-Simpson about her years inside the family home and her recollection of the day the murders took place.
title: Extended Cut: Eva Pilgrim’s sit-down with Murdaugh housekeeper Blanca Turrubiate-Simpson

author: Inside Edition
description: A fisherman, popular on YouTube, has reportedly been found dead days after going missing off the coast of Baja California Sur. Reports out of San Diego say Mikey Rijavec, who shared his passion for fishing on his channel SD Fish and Sips, was found near San Cristobal on November 16. Reports say he made a mayday call while on a solo outing on November 11. Rijavec had been sharing his adventures in fishing on YouTube for more than 10 years. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Mikey Rijavec of YouTube's SD Fish And Sips Found Dead Days After Mayday Call

author: Inside Edition
description: A TikTok influencer has died, allegedly shot dead by her boyfriend in Florida. The Broward County Sheriff's office says Maurice Harrison, 21, was shot in the front seat of a car in Lauderdale Lakes. She was taken to a hospital but died of her injuries. Harrison went by Girlalala on social media and fashioned herself a wig influencer, garnering nearly 300,000 followers on TikTok alone. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: TikTok Wig Influencer Girlalala Shot Dead In Florida

author: Inside Edition
description: Andrew, Alexander, and Tanner had been on a Thanksgiving visitation in 2010 with their dad, but when they were to return to their mother, they were missing. Their mother called the police. John Skelton told cops he gave his sons to a mysterious "underground organization."
title: Dad Of 3 Boys Who Went Missing In 2010 Faces Murder Charges #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Robyn Polston, 43, is being accused of having an affair with her daughter's 14-year-old boyfriend. The mother's former in-laws, Brendan Polston and Kira Grove, spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Woman Charged After Allegedly Conceiving Child With Teen #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Expect roads and airports to be jammed on Thanksgiving, but there's another place that also gets packed on Thanksgiving: the emergency room. Dr. Reed Caldwell, who runs the emergency department at NYU Langone Health, tells Inside Edition common injuries on the holiday are lacerations from sharp objects while chopping and cooking. Chef Michelle Doll Oslon gave Inside Edition some tips to help stay safe while cooking on Thanksgiving.
title: Tips To Avoid The Emergency Room On Thanksgiving

author: Inside Edition
description: Apparently bird flu wasn't just for the birds. Scientists with the British Antarctic Survey say one species on a remote island was hit hard by the outbreak. South Georgia Island lies in the southern Atlantic Ocean, east of Cape Horn and north of Antarctica. Researchers say the island lost 47 percent of its southern female elephant seals. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Bird Flu Kills Half Of Female Elephant Seals On Remote Island
